                <head>291. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>A letter of November 19 from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_AJM1"
                        >Allison</persName> to Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                        >Robertson</persName> is described by <persName corresp="#p_AJM1"
                        >Allison</persName> in <hi rend="italic">Ambassador From the Prairie</hi> as
                    stating that the Embassy had not been sufficiently informed of United States
                    policy and lacked officers with Indonesian experience and language training.
                        (<hi rend="italic">Ambassador From the Prairie,</hi> pages 333–334) The
                    letter has not been found in Department of State files. Telegram 1178 to
                    Djakarta, November 29, from <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> to
                        <persName corresp="#p_AJM1">Allison</persName> (cited in <pb facs="0537"
                        n="509" xml:id="pg_509"/>
                    <ref target="#d270">Document 270</ref>), stated, “I am shocked by situation
                    related your letter November 19, received today. Now making personal
                    investigation and will advise you further.”</p>
            </div>
